4️⃣ Build the P&L Page (Most Important Part)

Your manager specifically asked:

Find P&L for a particular period.

Create logic:

Total Sales = sum(total_price)
Total Cost = sum(cost_price * quantity)
Profit = Sales - Cost

Example Laravel logic:

$totalSales = Sale::sum('total_price');

$totalCost = Sale::join('items','sales.item_id','=','items.id')
->sum(DB::raw('items.cost_price * sales.quantity'));

$profit = $totalSales - $totalCost;
